The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, March 22, 2004  Business BriefsNew Delhi, March 21: Maruti Udyog Limited will increase prices next month due to rising input costs, especially steel. This was decided at a top-level meeting last week. It was proving difficult to absorb increasing input costs, company sources said. The quantum of the hike is yet to be decided. It is likely to be in line with the rise in input prices, which have gone up 3-4 per cent for compact cars like Wagon R in the past few months. Hyundai Motor India will also raise prices in April.
New Delhi, March 21: Data Access Indias initial public offer of five crore shares aimed at raising about Rs 100 crore is expected to open on March 29 and close on April 6. The offer will be conducted through the book-building route. Mumbai, March 21: Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC) has been added by Morgan Stanley Capital International in its standard index series with effect from April 1. This follows the successful mega offer for sale of the governments 10 per cent stake in ONGC aggregating over Rs 10,000 crore.
